{"TopicId":114888,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"[Answered] Distance between vessel and CelestialBody","CreatedByName":"simon56modder","CreatedById":119640,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-02T21:17:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"simon56modder","CreatedById":119640,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-02T21:17:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi, \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI want to know the distance (in meters preferably) between a Vessel v and a CelestialBody b, how can I do that ?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-07-02T21:41:19Z\u0022 title=\u002207/02/2015 09:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 2, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by simon56modder\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"simon56modder","CreatedById":119640,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-02T21:36:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Thomas P.\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Thomas P.\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ETry this:\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003EVector3.Distance(v.transform.position, b.transform.position)\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIs the returned value in meters ?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Crzyrndm","CreatedById":92871,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-02T21:39:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe scale is 1 unit : 1 meter\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat function is also probably just:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E(v.transform.position - b.transform.position).magnitude\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ewhich is more useful if you also need the direction vector for something\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-02T22:27:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThat will return the distance from the center of the body, if you care. You\u0027ll need to subtract the radius if you want the distance from the surface, and if you need really accurate numbers you\u0027ll need to get the terrain height.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}